Scala is an object oriented functional programming language. Scala source code is intended to be compiled to Java bytecode, so that the resulting executable code runs on a Java virtual machine. For this reason you will see many Java libraries used within Scala code.
*/

paragraphs.text: // Query 4. For every year, sum the contributions made to repositories created in this year

%sql
SELECT YEAR(r.createdAt), SUM(contributions)
FROM repositories r JOIN contributions c ON r.repositoryName = c.repository
GROUP BY YEAR(r.createdAt)
ORDER BY YEAR(r.createdAt) ASC
